{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The screen uses a vertical layout to present settings in a clear, sequential manner, consistent with mobile UX best practices.  Items are spaced 24px apart for visual breathing room and improved readability on smaller screens. Top and bottom padding are increased (48px) to provide ample space around the content and avoid cramped feel.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flows linearly down the settings list.  Selecting an item (which will be a List item component) should either launch a sub-screen (for more complex settings), or provide in-place modification (for simple settings like language). The bottom navigation bar enables easy movement between different sections of the app.",
    "componentChoices": "A Top app bar provides a consistent header, and a Bottom navigation bar offers quick access to other app sections. List items are used to display the settings clearly.  Text styles are used for visual consistency and hierarchy.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through: (1) Top app bar with the title having the highest prominence; (2)  Settings section header below the top app bar; (3) List items with clear labels and (4) the Bottom navigation bar with less prominent visual weight."
  },
